    "Two articles could not be retrieved because the authors or the corresponding title and abstract could not be identified online.",
    "Following full-text screening, 35 articles were excluded, and 89 articles were included in the final review.",
    "Most studies were excluded because they targeted the wrong discipline (n=10/35, 28.6%) or population (n=7/35, 20%) or were not original research (n=8/35, 22.9%) (see Supplementary Section 2).",
    "For example, we evaluated a study that focused on classifying physician notes to identify patients without active bleeding who were appropriate candidates for thromboembolism prophylaxis.",
